1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:10,160
<i>I'll go back to Pie with a job</i>
<i>and a future.</i>

2
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,760
But by the time you get back,
do you think Pie will wait for you?

3
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,960
I want you to give yourself a chance

4
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,400
and believe that you're good enough

5
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,120
to have a good man in your life.

6
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:27,640
Don't let past mistakes
close off opportunities for you.

7
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,240
Do you still want the same flower

8
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:33,760
<i>that you once said you liked</i>
<i>for your vase?</i>

9
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,480
I believe Pie is the right person for me.

10
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,160
I'm going to marry her.

11
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,720
- Marry?
- Marry?

12
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,880
Nhun!

13
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:47,960
I want you to see
that I'm serious and sincere.

14
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,960
That's why I said it in front of my mom,

15
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:53,920
to make things clear.

16
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,800
Pun and Pie.

17
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,640
- Mom wants to talk to you.
- Yes?

18
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:06,880
Alright.

19
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,720
<i>What do your parents do?</i>

20
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:22,280
My mom is a housewife,
and my dad is an investor.

21
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,720
What does he invest in?

22
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:27,320
Probably land and stocks, I think.

23
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,720
We haven't talked in a while.

24
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,920
My parents are divorced.

25
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,640
I live with my mom
because my dad has a new wife.

26
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:38,040
Does your dad still support you?

27
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,000
No.

28
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:43,040
How do you manage?
What's your income like?

29
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:46,800
Mom, I think you're asking too much.

30
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,400
It's okay, Pun.

31
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:51,400
I can answer. It's not a secret.

32
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,240
My income isn't very high.

33
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,080
I work alone.

34
00:03:57,160 --> 00:04:01,640
My mom earns from renting out
a condo she bought a while ago.

35
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,400
But it's not much.

36
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:08,520
The condo is in the suburbs,
not in the city.

37
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:11,920
It takes about an hour to get to Siam.

38
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:14,760
I see.

39
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,120
What's so funny?

40
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,320
She's speaking so honestly.

41
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,200
I like that about her, Dad.

42
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:23,640
Coming out strong and making bold moves.

43
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,360
But I won't let you marry her.

44
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,600
Mom, I'm an adult now.

45
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,280
When I speak, I mean it.

46
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:37,120
Are you arguing with me?

47
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:40,120
I'm not arguing, Mom.
I'm just confirming what I said.

48
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,840
In two days,
I'll ask Pie's mom for her hand.

49
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:48,080
If everything goes well,
we'll marry right away.

50
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,400
Pun!

51
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,880
Take it easy.

52
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,120
Pun.

53
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,120
Pie.

54
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,720
This is it. I've made up my mind.

55
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,560
Pun.

56
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,240
Were you joking when you said

57
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:37,120
that you were going to ask my mom
for her permission in two days?

58
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:40,160
And if she agrees,
you'll marry me right away?

59
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,840
You were just joking with your mom, right?

60
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,400
No, I wasn't joking.

61
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,440
I'm serious.

62
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,000
I mean it, and I'm going to do it.

63
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:52,240
But you haven't even asked me yet.

64
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:56,120
How can you talk about marriage
without asking the bride?

65
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:59,440
I was worried you'd think I was joking.

66
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,120
So I decided to talk about it
in front of my parents.

67
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,320
Hey.

68
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:11,440
I want you to be sure
that I'm serious and sincere.

69
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:14,520
I really want to marry you, Pie.

70
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:21,160
But you only asked me
to be your girlfriend yesterday.

71
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:24,280
Isn't it too soon to be talking
about marriage already?

72
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:28,880
If you've found the right person,
the timing doesn't matter.

73
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,040
Ever since I met you,

74
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,760
I've been imagining our wedding.

75
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,040
I don't think it's too soon.

76
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,000
There's no reason to wait anymore.

77
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,600
Marry me, Pie.

78
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:15,400
I really want to know
what that girl used to manipulate Pun.

79
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,720
How did he dare
to argue with me like that?

80
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,480
Is he being stubborn
because he's tired of you?

81
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:23,680
That girl seems harmless, even sweet.

82
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,800
Sweet poison!

83
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:28,600
She seems shy and sweet,
but I don't think she's that simple.

84
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,280
I don't trust her.

85
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,560
I won't let them get married.

86
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:38,960
It's because of you supporting him
that he dares to argue with me.

87
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,880
What's this about?

88
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:43,520
Come on. Pun's not a kid anymore.

89
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,000
You can't force him to do anything.

90
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:47,880
You'll just break the house apart.
Just let it go.

91
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,360
Nhun, if he wants to marry, let him.

92
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,960
If it doesn't work out, they'll divorce.

93
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,840
People get divorced easily nowadays.

94
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:57,800
I don't care.

95
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,320
I don't like that girl.

96
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,960
I don't want her as my daughter-in-law.

97
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:11,760
If his mom doesn't like you,
why should you care, Pie?

98
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,800
But she's his mom.
How can we not care, Mom?

99
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:18,240
You and that guy in Mae Hong Son
didn't seem to care about me.

100
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:26,720
I'm not trying to rub it in.
I'm just explaining.

101
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:29,760
When someone loves
or is infatuated with someone,

102
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:33,600
they don't care about anything else,
not even their own parents.

103
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:38,640
Besides, if he really loves you,
he'll fight through anything.

104
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:42,640
But I don't want to cause problems
for his family.

105
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:47,840
Pie, there won't be any problems
if Pun is on your side.

106
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,200
Trust me, sweetie.

107
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:52,160
Pun is the only son.

108
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,680
His mom won't be able to resist for long.

109
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:59,640
If her precious son truly wants something,
she'll eventually have to give in.

110
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:05,600
Honestly, Pun has won me over.

111
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:09,040
That's what a real son-in-law
should be like.

112
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:12,600
A real man who marries when he's ready.

113
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:14,240
If it's meant to be, he'll marry you.

114
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:16,280
Don't just take advantage.

115
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,440
Pie.

116
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:24,440
You're really lucky
to have found a man like Pun.

117
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,120
Is she pregnant?

118
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:43,440
Dad, why would you think that?

119
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,280
She's not pregnant.

120
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,280
Would you like some?

121
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,240
Thanks, Dad.

122
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:55,160
But if you're speaking for Mom,
I won't listen.

123
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:58,760
I'm not speaking for Mom.
I'm just warning you.

124
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,160
Are you sure you want to get married?

125
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:11,000
You know me, Dad.

126
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:13,600
I think things through before I do them.

127
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:17,360
I've planned everything, and I'm ready.

128
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,800
I plan to marry and have kids right away.

129
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:24,280
Isn't that a bit soon?

130
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,360
The sooner, the better.

131
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,160
Seriously, Dad.

132
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:32,840
I'm not that young anymore.
All my friends have kids already.

133
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:37,520
I don't want kids when I'm old
or using a cane at their graduation.

134
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,200
I want to have kids
while I'm still strong.

135
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:45,960
So I can travel, play sports,
golf, dive, and enjoy time with them.

136
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,160
What you're thinking sounds good.

137
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:52,960
But will your future wife agree with this?

138
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,640
Pie just graduated recently.

139
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,840
Does she really want kids already?

140
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,840
Pie is my girlfriend, Dad.

141
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,640
I can talk to her.

142
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,160
If I want kids,

143
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:07,320
she'll have them.

144
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,680
So you're sure about this one?

145
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,640
I've made my choice.

146
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:18,160
I've known Pie for a long time,
not just a day or two.

147
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,920
I'm sure I know her well.

148
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,360
This isn't just a fleeting emotion.

149
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,160
Alright.

150
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:28,160
Honestly, I like her too.

151
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:32,680
She doesn't seem like
the typical rich girls your mom picks.

152
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,160
She seems sincere.

153
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,640
See?

154
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,840
You only met her once, and you can tell.

155
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:44,560
I like that about her. She's sincere.

156
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,400
I don't get why Mom doesn't like her.

157
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,760
Your mom, she's all about status.

158
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,520
She doesn't like ordinary people.

159
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,080
She prefers high society.

160
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:01,480
But I hope time will make her accept Pie.

161
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,760
Even if Mom doesn't accept her,

162
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,080
she can't stop me.

163
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,000
Pie is the one I've chosen.

164
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:27,760
Eat this to relieve the stress.

165
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,360
Sugar fix. Eat first, diet later.

166
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,560
Go ahead.

167
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,840
- I'm digging in.
- Yeah.

168
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,080
How's it?

169
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,800
It's really good!

170
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,000
Eat more.

171
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,520
I feel better now. I ate something tasty.

172
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:57,240
- Thanks, Pie.
- No problem.

173
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,520
The cake's going to fall over.

174
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,520
You bought me so many treats.

175
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:06,560
You said you wanted to talk about Pun.
What's going on?

176
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:13,440
I agreed to be his girlfriend.

177
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:19,440
- Yes!
- Wait. Calm down.

178
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:21,600
- Is it true?
- Yeah.

179
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:25,680
And he took me to meet his parents.

180
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:27,400
Then he proposed to me.

181
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:30,080
- Huh? Pun proposed to you?
- Yeah.

182
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,880
- Pun proposed to you?!
- Yeah.

183
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:36,840
I love you! I'm so happy for you!

184
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:38,840
Calm down.

185
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:41,360
Pie!

186
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:44,360
But wait. I just don't get it.

187
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,120
Why is he so confident in me?

188
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,640
I'm not even confident in myself.

189
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:53,240
I never thought I'd be a good wife
or a good girlfriend to anyone.

190
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,480
Do you think he's doing this
to spite his parents?

191
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:59,880
I don't know. I feel like
he's kind of clashing with his mom.

192
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,760
You're overthinking.

193
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:04,640
Pun loves you unconditionally.

194
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,280
And he's ready.

195
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:09,600
You see, many celebrity couples
date for a while and get married.

196
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,520
Don't worry about it.

197
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,440
Pun is very sincere and serious about you.

198
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:16,560
Yeah, I know that.

199
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:19,480
He's a great guy. My mom likes him too.

200
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:21,640
If marriage makes my mom happy,
I'm fine with it.

201
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,560
Congrats, girl!

202
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:27,560
I'm so happy for you.

203
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,440
What do you need to do next?

204
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:36,560
I heard Pun wants to bring
his parents to talk to my mom.

205
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:37,960
What? When?

206
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:39,120
Tomorrow.

207
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,040
Tomorrow?

208
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:43,000
Rok!

209
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,240
My ears can't handle this!

210
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:47,240
- Really? Oh my God!
- Yeah.

211
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,120
- So exciting!
- Are you excited?

212
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,800
- Yes!
- You're excited.

213
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,320
Eat this.

214
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,520
- My ears are going to explode.
- Fine, I'll eat.

215
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,840
I don't want to go.

216
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,200
Your son is asking for her hand.

217
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:11,960
As a mother, how can you not go?

218
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,880
But I don't want their daughter.

219
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:17,800
Pun, think about it again.

220
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:19,000
Take your time getting to know each other.

221
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,520
No need to rush marriage.

222
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,640
If you rush into marriage,
what will people think?

223
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,960
Mom.

224
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:26,920
I don't care what people think.
I don't care about society's opinions.

225
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,720
Besides, I'm just an ordinary guy.

226
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:29,920
No one cares about me.

227
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,200
But you're my son.

228
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,800
Many people know me.

229
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:35,080
You're my son too.

230
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,760
Not many people know me. Don't worry.

231
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,600
Hey, why are you arguing with me?

232
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:42,240
He should have the right
to choose which path to follow.

233
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,520
Then I'll follow Dad's path.

234
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,200
Low profile, but high profit.

235
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,760
I've made my decision, Mom.
If you're not going,

236
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,760
- I'll go with Dad.
- I'm leaving.

237
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:55,080
Wait, I'll go too.

238
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:58,760
If it's just the two of you,
you'll both be too soft-hearted.

239
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:01,200
If they ask for a high bride price,
you'll give in.

240
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,280
I won't let anyone take advantage.

241
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,800
I'll go myself.

242
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,160
Pie.

243
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,520
Come here quickly.

244
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,120
Sit down here. Hurry up.

245
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,360
- Come on.
- Yes, Mom.

246
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:25,960
Come look at this quickly.

247
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,920
Look at this, Pie.

248
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,320
What do you think?

249
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,000
Do I look rich?

250
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:34,600
I invested
in renting these authentic items.

251
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,560
You look very rich, Mom.

252
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,600
Isn't this too much for our status?

253
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:41,160
Well, it's good.

254
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:45,800
Though Pun knows we're low
on money, his parents don't.

255
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,920
I still need some nice accessories.

256
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,880
That way, they won't look down on us.

257
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:51,200
Alright?

258
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:58,840
Mom, where's Puk?
Why are there so many maids?

259
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:00,440
I gave her time off.

260
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:04,240
If she stayed and embarrassed us,
it'd be worse.

261
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:07,119
As for these three, I hired them.

262
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,920
- Huh? You hired them?
- Yeah.

263
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,119
Why did you hire them?

264
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,920
Well, to show off a little.

265
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,599
Let me introduce them one by one.

266
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:18,720
Come here, ladies.

267
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:24,079
This is Som-O, Bai Tong, and Jiew.

268
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:27,760
These three have played maids
in many times before already.

269
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:29,040
They're the best at what they do.

270
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:32,120
As for the outfits, look at this, Pie.

271
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,680
I rented them from a film set.

272
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:35,640
What do you think? Are they neat?

273
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,120
Hello!

274
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,880
The madam and young lady
are waiting inside.

275
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,120
Please, come in.

276
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:05,000
So many maids. Quite impressive.

277
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,080
You can't judge just by this.

278
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:09,120
People today like to put on a show.

279
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,920
Should we ask to see their accounts?

280
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,640
If we can, sure.

281
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,840
The guests are here, madam.

282
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,040
Pie, they're here.

283
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,720
Hello.

284
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:36,800
I'm Tubtim, Pie's mother.

285
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:46,960
- Aunt Tubtim, this is my dad and mom.
- Hello.

286
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,200
Nice to meet you.

287
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:50,760
Likewise.

288
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:54,240
By the way, have you eaten yet?

289
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:55,520
Not yet.

290
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:59,160
Pun rushed us here.
He's so excited that we haven't eaten.

291
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:01,080
Well, perfect.

292
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:04,120
I've prepared some snacks.

293
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:06,400
They're traditional Thai desserts.

294
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:08,120
Really delicious.

295
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:11,320
Let's have some snacks first
before we talk.

296
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,440
- That's great.
- No.

297
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:13,600
We're not hungry.

298
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:20,920
Let's get to the point,
so we can leave soon.

299
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,240
Please, help yourself.

300
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:41,040
Let's get to the point.
I don't want to waste time.

301
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,280
How much is the bride price?

302
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:46,880
I didn't raise my daughter
to sell her off.

303
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:51,920
Well, in that case,
there's no need for a bride price.

304
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,280
Just get married quietly.

305
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:55,080
- Mom.
- No!

306
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,600
What? You just said
you're not selling her.

307
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,960
Mom.

308
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,120
I'm not selling her.

309
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:13,080
But marriage needs a bride price.

310
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,200
It's a tradition.

311
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,800
You say one thing, but mean another.

312
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:27,080
I intend to give it anyway.

313
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,080
Is this enough?

314
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:37,840
Let me see first.

315
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,040
FIFTY MILLION BAHT

316
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:49,160
- Is this too much?
- Mom.

317
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,040
Can I see it, Pun?

318
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:55,920
- Not yet.
- Let me see it, Pun.

319
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:57,920
- I said no.
- Let me see.

320
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,160
- Mom.
- I said no!

321
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,440
- Let me see!
- Not yet!

322
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,440
Let me see!

323
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:02,680
- No need to!
- Let me see!

324
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,440
That's enough, Mom.

325
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,040
Let Aunt Tubtim see it, please.

326
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:15,880
Or should I offer more?

327
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,520
Go ahead, look.

328
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,360
Honestly,

329
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:40,920
I'm not too concerned
about the bride price.

330
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:44,480
Just go with what Pun suggests. It's fine.

331
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:45,600
Then take half of it.

332
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,200
The part that's torn off.

333
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,640
I thought you weren't concerned?

334
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,440
You seem rich on the outside.

335
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,840
Why need such a high bride price?

336
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:07,080
I don't want anything that's too much.

337
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,080
Pie!

338
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,520
You never think about these things.

339
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:16,040
I'll handle it for you, okay?

340
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,520
I'll talk to them.

341
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:25,000
You don't want anything.

342
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,520
But your mom does, huh?

343
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:32,520
Aunt Tubtim,
please don't listen to my mom.

344
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:36,760
I want to give this to Pie.

345
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,040
And that's it.

346
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:39,760
Pun!

347
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,000
Are you okay with this, Ms. Tubtim?

348
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:49,920
Honestly, I'm an easygoing person.

349
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,720
Whatever works.

350
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,440
I'm fine with Pun's suggestion.

351
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,720
It's settled.

352
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,080
Alright.

353
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,640
Okay then.

354
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:15,080
Why did you agree so easily?

355
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:17,080
Our son isn't a nobody.

356
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:20,520
Come on. Our son agreed to it.

357
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,480
That's why they're taking advantage.

358
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:24,840
Did you see that mom?
She's not keeping it together.

359
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:28,040
Her daughter will be set
once she marries into this family.

360
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:30,880
She wants the money.

361
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:34,800
That woman is really something!

362
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:38,680
She talks down to us like we have nothing
and thinks we're eyeing her son.

363
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:42,440
Do you know how hard your son
has been courting my daughter?

364
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:44,160
Be careful, Pun.

365
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,880
Like mother, like daughter.

366
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,600
She looks sweet, innocent, and all nice.

367
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:50,600
But she's just pretending.

368
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:52,400
She's trying to get something out of you.

369
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:56,400
That woman acts like she doesn't want
to offer the bride price.

370
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:58,960
She's rich but stingy!

371
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:02,920
Or maybe she's not actually rich,
which is why she's being so cheap.

372
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:06,040
Mom, I don't care if they're rich or not.

373
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:08,600
I don't care either,
whether they're poor or rich.

374
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:12,280
I have enough.
I don't want anything from them.

375
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:15,760
I don't want anything from anyone.
I want to earn it myself.

376
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:18,000
Anyway, I'm not okay with this.

377
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,800
I don't trust this girl.

378
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,280
I think she's not as good as she seems.

379
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:24,680
Pie, don't mind that woman at all.

380
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:27,320
You're marrying the son, not the mother.

381
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,800
No need to care. Keep that in mind.

382
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,120
I agree with your mom, you know.

383
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:38,000
Aunt Nhun is really being extra.
My mom's family…

384
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:44,400
My mom's family doesn't get along with her
and she doesn't want anyone either.

385
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:48,560
I can already tell
she doesn't want my family either.

386
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:51,320
Hey, don't stress.

387
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,480
Above Aunt Nhun,
there's still Pun, you know.

388
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:56,000
And I'm sure Pun loves you a lot.

389
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:58,040
Everything will work out.

390
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:00,960
I hope that's true.

391
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:04,680
Pun can clear everything up.

392
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:08,400
I'm really happy for you.
You're going to get married.

393
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,720
Congrats!

394
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:17,960
Pun will definitely take
good care of you. Don't worry.

395
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,760
You'll be happy, Pie.

396
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:23,920
I really appreciate you, Rok.
Thank you so much.

397
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,280
So when's the wedding?

398
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:30,120
Well, Pun said he's looking
for an auspicious date.

399
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:32,080
But I already told him I'm not in a hurry.

400
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,960
You want to get married
as soon as possible?

401
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,240
Yeah.

402
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:40,440
Why? When you find the right person,
just marry them.

403
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:45,080
Seriously, did you get her pregnant?

404
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,200
You're crazy.

405
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:48,800
I don't get why people
keep asking me that.

406
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,320
My dad asked the same.

407
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,760
Everything's happening so fast.
It's all sudden.

408
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:54,760
You just started seeing her.

409
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:56,640
Honestly,

410
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:59,560
I started noticing her
when I was a guest lecturer for you.

411
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:07,280
This is like the shepherd
sneaking around eating the sheep.

412
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:10,000
And his friend's sheep too!

413
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,520
I wasn't sneaking around!

414
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:13,240
What could I do?

415
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,280
The first time I met Pie,
I was already hooked.

416
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,320
Before I knew it,
I was falling for your student.

417
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:23,760
I'm honestly surprised myself.

418
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:26,400
I've never felt like this
about anyone before.

419
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,800
Pie's the first.

420
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:32,880
That's why I'm sure she's the one for me.

421
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:37,480
So smooth.

422
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:40,360
That sounds like a wedding speech.

423
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:48,880
Our groom, Mr. Pun!

424
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,080
I'm serious though.

425
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,320
Awesome.

426
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:59,880
ENGLAND

427
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:27,960
DEGREE HUNTER

428
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:31,320
<i>You guys better lose some weight</i>
<i>because this year,</i>

429
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:34,080
<i>someone's going to be</i>
<i>the first bride in the group.</i>

430
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,800
<i>And that person is…</i>

431
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:39,000
<i>Mrs. Pie!</i>

432
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,320
<i>Rok, tone it down a bit.</i>

433
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:44,480
<i>- What's this all about?</i>
<i>- Good news should be announced.</i>

434
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:47,120
<i>Pie's going to marry my older brother.</i>

435
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:49,520
<i>Professor Pun, who gave us</i>
<i>bad grades. Remember?</i>

436
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:01,800
<i>Yay!</i>

437
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:02,880
<i>Congrats!</i>

438
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,120
<i>Better lose weight fast.</i>

439
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:06,320
<i>Congrats!</i>

440
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:08,520
DEGREE HUNTER

441
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:09,880
LEAVE

442
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,280
- Hey.
- What?

443
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:13,480
Mink left the group.

444
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:17,520
It's because you announced my wedding.

445
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:19,720
That's obvious.

446
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:22,520
I forgot Mink was still in the group.

447
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:25,160
Sorry, Mink.

448
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,680
I should text her to apologize.

449
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,920
It's clear she still
hasn't gotten over Pun.

450
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:48,160
NAGOYA, JAPAN

451
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:24,920
MAE HONG SON

452
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:48,280
SILPAKORN

453
00:29:57,720 --> 00:30:00,200
A double rainbow means love.

454
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:03,040
They say if you see one,

455
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:05,120
people who once loved each other
will meet again.

456
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:49,400
DONATION ITEMS

457
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:54,480
<i>The right person at the wrong time</i>
<i>is still the wrong person.</i>

458
00:30:54,560 --> 00:31:00,440
<i>And the wrong person at the right time</i>
<i>is also still not the right one.</i>

459
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:10,560
<i>How does this relate to my ex,</i>
<i>whom I still can't forget?</i>

460
00:31:11,280 --> 00:31:14,320
<i>Well, at that time, you loved him,</i>

461
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,200
<i>but you weren't ready, right?</i>

462
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,520
<i>That means he wasn't the right one.</i>

463
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:19,120
That's right.

464
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:27,520
<i>But now, you're totally ready.</i>

465
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:30,920
<i>You want a family,</i>
<i>you want kids before your eggs dry up,</i>

466
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:35,080
<i>but if the person isn't right,</i>
<i>it still won't work. Understand?</i>

467
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,440
Totally!

468
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:44,440
<i>So, the right person will come</i>
<i>at the right time, when everything aligns.</i>

469
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:49,800
<i>If everything is right,</i>
<i>things will happen easily and quickly.</i>

470
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:52,280
<i>So, no need to rush.</i>

471
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:55,840
<i>If it's the right time and place,</i>

472
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:59,280
<i>it will work out on its own.</i>

473
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:02,320
<i>Pek. Do you think I'll ever find one?</i>

474
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:04,240
<i>I don't know.</i>

475
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,640
<i>But you know what?</i>

476
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:12,040
<i>If you don't find him,</i>
<i>you won't die, right?</i>

477
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:16,200
<i>I've never heard of someone dying</i>
<i>from being single.</i>

478
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:19,680
<i>So, let's focus on taking care</i>
<i>of ourselves</i>

479
00:32:20,280 --> 00:32:21,480
<i>and living well.</i>

480
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:29,760
<i>If it's the right time and place,</i>
<i>you'll meet the right person.</i>

481
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:30,880
<i>Good luck.</i>

482
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:40,240
<i>But you only asked me</i>
<i>to be your girlfriend yesterday.</i>

483
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:43,000
Isn't it too soon to be talking
about marriage already?

484
00:32:43,080 --> 00:32:46,200
If you've found the right person,
the timing doesn't matter.

485
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,680
Marry me, Pie.

486
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:19,800
FOUR MONTHS LATER

487
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:23,200
- Pie.
- Yes, Pun?

488
00:33:24,120 --> 00:33:27,600
I've set the wedding date.
It's on June 11th.

489
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:30,800
You said it would be
at the end of the year.

490
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:33,000
There's no available date
at the end of the year.

491
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:37,520
But June is only a few months away.

492
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:41,160
Don't worry, Pie.
I've already arranged everything.

493
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:51,720
Here.

494
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:54,400
This is the engagement room.

495
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:58,640
And this is the room for the wedding.

496
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:00,480
For the food,

497
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,960
I've chosen a buffet
and pre-selected a menu.

498
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:05,320
These are the wedding favors.

499
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:07,680
Essential oils from my friend.

500
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:09,760
He exports them internationally.

501
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:13,159
I've also ordered a special scent,
so no one else will have it.

502
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:18,320
And the wedding dress,
I've already chosen it.

503
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,880
The designer is really good.

504
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,719
I'm sure you'll love it.

505
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:29,440
Have a look.

506
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:36,800
Don't you like it?

507
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:39,679
I like it.

508
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:42,520
I knew you'd like it.

509
00:34:43,199 --> 00:34:45,840
I'm only picking the best for you.

510
00:34:52,560 --> 00:34:53,800
Pun.

511
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:58,400
Honestly, you could have let me help
with some things.

512
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:00,680
You've planned everything.

513
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:03,000
I'm going to be the laziest bride ever.

514
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:05,440
About the food,

515
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:07,280
how about switching to a Chinese banquet?

516
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,880
It'll be easier on the older guests.

517
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,440
Just stick with my plan.

518
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:18,760
You don't have to do anything, Pie.

519
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:22,560
Just show up as the bride
on the wedding day.

520
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:25,280
I'll send you the schedule by email.

521
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:27,760
The schedule by email?

522
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:31,440
It's the event schedule.

523
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,400
I'm the wedding planner.

524
00:35:33,480 --> 00:35:36,640
No one does it the way I want,
so I'll handle it myself.

525
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,680
Pie, the reason
I won't let you do anything

526
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:49,920
is because I've seen many couples
who get along well

527
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:52,640
but end up fighting on their wedding day.

528
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:55,000
I don't want to fight with you.

529
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:58,280
So I've taken care of everything for you.

530
00:35:58,880 --> 00:36:02,440
I know you trust me.

531
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:05,680
You're easygoing.

532
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:07,680
You'll be fine with everything.

533
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:16,560
- Yes.
- You're the sweetest.

534
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:58,960
Pie, smile.

535
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,480
- Show a big smile.
- Ms. Tubtim.

536
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:01,600
Stop directing. Come here.

537
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:02,760
Let's take a photo together.

538
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,520
- Come on.
- Okay, I'm happy to.

539
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:06,520
Please, come this way.

540
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:08,200
Family photo.

541
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:09,960
My daughter's getting married. I'm happy.

542
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:11,600
Mom, please smile.

543
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,520
Wait a minute. I want to switch places.

544
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:18,800
Nhun, move over there.

545
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:20,160
No, I want to stay here.

546
00:37:20,240 --> 00:37:22,160
Fine, stay here.

547
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:24,040
- Look at you.
- Okay, ready.

548
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:25,600
You're messing around.

549
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,720
- Smile.
- Smile too.

550
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:32,520
Smile, my dear.

551
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:40,200
Pun and Pie.

552
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:43,160
- Sil, hello.
- Hello.

553
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:46,000
Welcome to the family, my dear.

554
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:50,080
You're so beautiful. So beautiful.

555
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:53,320
- I feel like I could die.
- Oh my, you're too much!

556
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:54,680
Congratulations, Pun.

557
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:56,960
Congrats, girl. Wishing
you both lasting love.

558
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:57,920
Of course.

559
00:38:02,160 --> 00:38:03,120
Nhun.

560
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:07,440
- Pun, I'll be right back. Nhun.
- Sure.

561
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:09,000
You're going to be my sister-in-law.

562
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:11,560
I never imagined
we'd be related like this.

563
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,840
Nhun, where are you going?

564
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:17,120
Let's take some photos.

565
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:18,960
Just take them.

566
00:38:19,040 --> 00:38:22,320
What do you mean?
Let's take them together.

567
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:24,120
It looks bad walking away like this.

568
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:27,480
When will your friends be here?

569
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:31,480
I only invited Dech.
I didn't invite the others.

570
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:35,440
What's with you?
Your son is getting married.

571
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:37,560
He's marrying someone I don't know.

572
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:40,560
I want to keep it as quiet as possible.

573
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:43,280
When they break up,
I won't have to explain anything.

574
00:38:45,240 --> 00:38:47,960
Sil, let's take some photos!

575
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:49,680
Wait, where's Nhun?

576
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:50,800
I don't know.

577
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:54,040
Let's just take photos
with whoever is here.

578
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:55,200
What's going on?

579
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:00,560
- Let's go out first.
- Where are you going?

580
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:01,920
- Where are we going?
- Where to?

581
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:04,120
- Let them take the couple's pictures.
- Got it!

582
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:07,480
- Okay.
- Let's take it together.

583
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:10,560
Get closer, cheeks together.

584
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:12,320
- Cheeks touching.
- That's it.

585
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:15,280
Hug each other tightly, Pie. Exactly!

586
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:17,240
Kiss if you want to.

587
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:18,480
- Kiss!
- Mom!

588
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:21,760
- Kiss!
- Really?

589
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:23,200
Kiss!

590
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:25,840
- Look into each other's eyes.
- Yeah.

591
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,160
Strike a pose!

592
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:32,160
I'm so happy!

593
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:38,960
<i>Congratulations, PP The Wedding.</i>

594
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:44,160
Hope it works out for you.

595
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:01,560
The groom's mother
is hiding here, drinking wine!

596
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:04,000
Where are our friends?
I can't find them anywhere.

597
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:07,160
I only invited you.

598
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,840
I didn't want a big crowd.

599
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,840
As for the important guests,

600
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:12,680
I had to invite them.

601
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:16,360
I'm being honest. I'm not okay with this.

602
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,560
Hey, Nhun.

603
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:21,880
Those two kids are getting married.
Get used to it.

604
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:24,280
I can't handle it.

605
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:27,640
That girl's mother is fake,
acting all rich,

606
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:31,560
but she's scrambling to pay off
her credit card debt every month.

607
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:34,880
How do you know that?

608
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:38,080
I have a financial investigator.

609
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:39,600
All show, no substance.

610
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:43,080
That's scary.

611
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:45,600
That girl and her mother?

612
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:47,240
No, you!

613
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:48,520
Hey.

614
00:40:48,600 --> 00:40:52,480
Checking other people's credit card debt
is illegal, you know?

615
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:55,920
Just keep quiet and don't tell anyone.

616
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:59,480
I don't even want to believe it's true.

617
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,880
I've found him so many women,
but he rejects them all.

618
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:06,120
Well, those two kids
really love each other.

619
00:41:06,720 --> 00:41:08,360
I don't believe they love each other.

620
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:12,240
Pun is just marrying someone to spite me.

621
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,000
Just wait and see. They won't last.

622
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:15,200
They'll break up for sure.

623
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:11,680
Pun.

624
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:15,320
Good morning, my wife.

625
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:17,560
Good morning, Pun.

626
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:20,200
You must be tired from last night.

627
00:42:21,600 --> 00:42:23,320
You can still sleep if you want.

628
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:27,400
I'll do some work first,
then come get you to take you home.

629
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:29,200
Okay.

630
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:34,760
I ordered food that's good
for giving you energy.

631
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:35,960
Make sure to eat it all.

632
00:42:36,560 --> 00:42:37,440
Okay.

633
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,040
I've already told the maid
to clean the house.

634
00:42:41,120 --> 00:42:45,000
I also spoke to your mom
and arranged for your things to be moved.

635
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:46,800
You can move in today.

636
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,640
You don't have to move
everything yourself.

637
00:42:49,720 --> 00:42:50,640
Okay.

638
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:55,680
Eat everything, okay?

639
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:58,920
Once I've taken care of everything,
we can go home.

640
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,080
I don't like waiting.

641
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:02,960
Okay.

642
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:08,080
See you.

643
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,080
Let's go.

644
00:43:43,680 --> 00:43:45,480
Good morning, sir.

645
00:43:47,080 --> 00:43:49,760
- Good morning, ma'am.
- Hello.

646
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:53,920
Bring the things
from the car trunk to our house.

647
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:03,480
What do you think? Do you like it?

648
00:44:04,040 --> 00:44:06,280
I built this with us three in mind.

649
00:44:06,800 --> 00:44:07,960
Us three?

650
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:11,880
Yes, I've prepared a room for our baby.

651
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:15,560
Pun, isn't it too soon?
We just got married.

652
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:16,960
Pie.

653
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:21,880
I got married
because I want a complete family.

654
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:25,640
I want to be a father
and for you to be our child's mother.

655
00:44:26,440 --> 00:44:28,960
I know you'll be a great mom.

656
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:34,880
Let's make a baby.

657
00:44:34,960 --> 00:44:35,960
Pun!

658
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:39,080
Pun, wait!

659
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:40,960
Right now, okay?

660
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:44,560
Pun!

661
00:44:46,880 --> 00:44:48,040
Hey, Sil!

662
00:44:48,960 --> 00:44:51,760
No phones at the dining table.
Don't you remember?

663
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,000
We haven't started eating yet.

664
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:55,360
You see our son arguing with me

665
00:44:55,440 --> 00:44:57,480
and disobeying my orders.
Are you following him?

666
00:44:57,560 --> 00:44:58,480
Nhun.

667
00:44:58,560 --> 00:45:00,520
Don't make a big deal
out of something trivial.

668
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:03,320
I'll put it away,
following your orders. Okay?

669
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:06,800
Tian, serve the food
before she gets too hangry.

670
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:07,760
Yes, sir.

671
00:45:10,200 --> 00:45:12,520
Didn't Pun and that girl come to eat?

672
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:15,600
I told them both to rest
after the event. They're tired.

673
00:45:15,680 --> 00:45:17,920
The maid prepared something simple
for the two of them.

674
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:19,000
Well.

675
00:45:19,640 --> 00:45:20,920
That's fitting.

676
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:23,160
A simple girl with simple food.

677
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:26,320
You need to let go
of some of your stubbornness.

678
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,120
Or we won't be able to live together.

679
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:31,000
I won't let go. I'll stay the way I am.

680
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:32,920
This house is mine.

681
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:36,000
If that girl moves in here,
she'll have to follow my rules.

682
00:45:36,080 --> 00:45:38,480
If she can't handle it, she can leave.

683
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:56,840
Oh, you don't want anything.

684
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,280
But your mom does, huh?

685
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:01,320
You're marrying the son, not the mother.

686
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:03,240
<i>No need to care. Keep that in mind.</i>

687
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:33,560
<i>And I'm sure Pun loves you a lot.</i>

688
00:46:33,640 --> 00:46:36,000
<i>Everything will work out.</i>

689
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:48,840
Mainly, I'm going to Nagoya.

690
00:46:48,920 --> 00:46:50,800
The rest will depend
on where Fon takes me.

691
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:52,480
<i>I want to go too.</i>

692
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:55,160
Tell Pun to take you on a honeymoon.

693
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:58,000
If you want to make it better,
have him cover the travel costs

694
00:46:58,080 --> 00:46:59,320
and bring me along too,

695
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:02,760
since I'm the reason
you and Pun got together.

696
00:47:02,840 --> 00:47:05,160
<i>Consider it a consolation trip for me</i>

697
00:47:05,240 --> 00:47:06,680
after Tay cheated on me.

698
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:09,160
Thinking about it still makes me angry.

699
00:47:09,240 --> 00:47:13,880
Rok, you caught the bouquet at my wedding!

700
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:16,720
You'll definitely meet
some nice guys on this trip.

701
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:18,120
Yeah, you're right.

702
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:19,400
One, two, three.

703
00:47:26,120 --> 00:47:30,240
I got really drunk and don't even remember
where I put the bouquet.

704
00:47:31,440 --> 00:47:33,320
What does that mean, Pie?

705
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:34,840
Will I mess it up?

706
00:47:36,040 --> 00:47:37,840
Hey, have fun on your trip.

707
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:39,080
Say hi to Fon for me.

708
00:47:39,160 --> 00:47:42,160
<i>Bye. We'll talk later. Have fun!</i>

709
00:47:42,240 --> 00:47:44,800
Okay. Kisses. Bye.

710
00:47:49,520 --> 00:47:51,080
This trip can't go wrong, right?

711
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:53,240
I'm going to meet someone
this time for sure.

712
00:48:00,080 --> 00:48:01,520
Oh my gosh!

713
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:05,000
Pie, the house is beautiful!

714
00:48:05,080 --> 00:48:08,160
So stylish. I really like it! Look!

715
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,760
This place is so Instagrammable.

716
00:48:10,840 --> 00:48:13,040
Oh, it's so beautiful!

717
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:15,720
Wow, Pie!

718
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:17,560
The picture is so big!

719
00:48:17,640 --> 00:48:21,400
Oh my goodness, I love it!
It's so cozy, so cute.

720
00:48:23,320 --> 00:48:24,160
- Pie.
- Yes?

721
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:27,000
Did you separate the gift envelopes
from the guests on my side?

722
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:28,320
I didn't separate them.

723
00:48:28,400 --> 00:48:30,400
Huh? Why not, Pie?

724
00:48:30,480 --> 00:48:33,560
I told you to separate them,
so I could come and get them today.

725
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:37,520
I didn't separate them
because Pun gave me everything.

726
00:48:37,600 --> 00:48:39,680
And I will give it all to you.

727
00:48:39,760 --> 00:48:42,840
Hey, don't you want
to keep some for yourself?

728
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:45,520
But Pun probably won't allow it.

729
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:48,400
I'll just take everything then.

730
00:48:48,480 --> 00:48:51,080
- So Pun won't be upset.
- Mom.

731
00:48:51,160 --> 00:48:53,400
Why, Pie? I'll just take the envelope…

732
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:58,600
By the way, yesterday,
all the guests at the wedding

733
00:48:58,680 --> 00:49:01,280
were famous people!

734
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:03,880
Mr. Charoenpon came too, you know.

735
00:49:03,960 --> 00:49:05,400
What did he give you?

736
00:49:05,480 --> 00:49:07,360
Did he put money
in an envelope, give a gift,

737
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:08,800
or transfer money?

738
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:12,520
It was a gift. I saw his business card
when I was cleaning up around here.

739
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:14,880
Really? Which box was it?
Where is the business card?

740
00:49:15,520 --> 00:49:18,320
- Let me see it.
- Mom.

741
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:22,880
Here it is, this box! Found it!

742
00:49:22,960 --> 00:49:25,120
Pie, I really want to see what's inside.

743
00:49:25,200 --> 00:49:26,520
Let me open it.

744
00:49:26,600 --> 00:49:29,400
Mom, maybe Pun should open it.

745
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:31,360
It's just one box.

746
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:33,560
Pun gave us all the envelopes.

747
00:49:33,640 --> 00:49:35,440
So this box shouldn't be a problem.

748
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:37,280
- Let me just open it.
- Mom.

749
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:40,520
What's inside? Let's see.

750
00:49:41,120 --> 00:49:42,600
Take everything back.

751
00:49:42,680 --> 00:49:45,400
And don't lose
the business cards on the gifts.

752
00:49:56,800 --> 00:49:58,840
Hello, Nhun.

753
00:50:02,120 --> 00:50:03,080
Tian.

754
00:50:08,680 --> 00:50:10,880
What's going on? Wait, stop.

755
00:50:10,960 --> 00:50:12,600
Where are you taking that?

756
00:50:12,680 --> 00:50:15,760
I need to account
for what each guest gave us.

757
00:50:15,840 --> 00:50:18,840
When they have an event, we can give them

758
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:20,320
at least as much in return.

759
00:50:20,400 --> 00:50:23,560
You probably haven't done this before.

760
00:50:28,240 --> 00:50:30,240
Take it all to my house,
including the envelopes.

761
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:33,240
Wait, stop!

762
00:50:33,320 --> 00:50:35,600
I told you to stop! Back off!

763
00:50:36,640 --> 00:50:37,800
Don't touch them.

764
00:50:37,880 --> 00:50:39,880
Pun gave the money envelopes to Pie.

765
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:41,320
They can't be taken back.

766
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:44,360
Mom, let her take it.

767
00:50:44,440 --> 00:50:46,680
Pie, Pun gave you the money.

768
00:50:46,760 --> 00:50:48,120
So it's ours now.

769
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:50,480
I don't want the money.

770
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:52,720
I don't want any of these things.

771
00:50:53,320 --> 00:50:54,960
I just want to record

772
00:50:55,040 --> 00:50:57,320
how much each guest gave,
and I'll return them to you.

773
00:50:57,400 --> 00:50:59,720
I don't need the money from the envelopes.

774
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:02,720
They just gave it as a social courtesy.

775
00:51:04,720 --> 00:51:05,920
People like me

776
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:09,000
don't go around fighting
for money in envelopes.

777
00:51:09,640 --> 00:51:11,160
If you want it, take it.

778
00:51:12,720 --> 00:51:15,120
But if you want to learn proper etiquette,

779
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:17,360
keep track of how much people give.

780
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:19,080
Next time, if they invite us to an event,

781
00:51:19,160 --> 00:51:22,120
we'll give them more than they gave us.

782
00:51:22,200 --> 00:51:23,840
So they won't gossip behind our backs.

783
00:51:25,240 --> 00:51:26,400
But the question is,

784
00:51:26,480 --> 00:51:28,840
do you have enough money to give back?

785
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:33,080
Because my guests give big envelopes.

786
00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:35,680
I'm not looking down on anyone.

787
00:51:35,760 --> 00:51:37,480
I'm just pointing it out.

788
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:10,280
You're right, Nhun.

789
00:52:10,360 --> 00:52:14,240
We won't be comfortable
giving a large amount in envelopes.

790
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:17,640
What I can do is open the envelopes,

791
00:52:17,720 --> 00:52:20,040
- take notes, and give them to Pun!
- Mom!

792
00:52:20,120 --> 00:52:22,880
After all, Pun is responsible
for managing our image.

793
00:52:22,960 --> 00:52:26,520
Don't you ever forget
that Pie is now Pun's wife.

794
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:30,040
Whatever the wife does,
it reflects on the husband.

795
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:33,280
If people gossip behind our backs,

796
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:35,240
they'll drag the family into it.

797
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:36,760
And if things go badly,

798
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:38,520
it could even hurt your reputation.

799
00:52:39,120 --> 00:52:42,120
We're in the same boat now.

800
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:44,040
We're a family.

801
00:52:44,120 --> 00:52:45,880
My child even carries your last name.

802
00:52:45,960 --> 00:52:47,840
Instead of being enemies,

803
00:52:47,920 --> 00:52:49,480
wouldn't it be better to get along?!

804
00:52:51,160 --> 00:52:52,320
Are you threatening me?

805
00:52:52,400 --> 00:52:54,880
I'm not threatening you.
I'm just speaking logically.

806
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:57,320
Sounds more like extortion.

807
00:52:57,400 --> 00:52:58,440
You'll take the money,

808
00:52:58,520 --> 00:53:00,800
but won't give back the envelope money.

809
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,920
You want my son to pay for it, huh?

810
00:53:03,000 --> 00:53:06,120
Oh, please, this won't hurt Pun at all.

811
00:53:06,200 --> 00:53:07,680
You don't need to be so stingy
for your son.

812
00:53:07,760 --> 00:53:09,040
Mom, enough!

813
00:53:09,120 --> 00:53:10,240
I'm not being stingy!

814
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:12,240
I don't like being taken advantage of.

815
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:14,720
You just moved in,

816
00:53:14,800 --> 00:53:16,640
and already your true nature is showing.

817
00:53:16,720 --> 00:53:19,400
If you stay longer, I don't know
how much more you'll take from me.

818
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:21,760
I knew I couldn't trust you.

819
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:23,200
I'm sorry, Nhun.

820
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:26,160
We've never extorted anyone
or asked for anything.

821
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:28,360
It's always been your son who offered.

822
00:53:28,440 --> 00:53:29,560
If you don't believe me, ask anyone.

823
00:53:29,640 --> 00:53:30,920
Mom, enough! Let's go home!

824
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:32,200
- No, Pie!
- Mom, let's go!

825
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:33,760
- I won't let her talk down to us.
- Mom!

826
00:53:33,840 --> 00:53:36,800
- I won't let her look down on us. Let go!
- Mom, let's go home.

827
00:53:36,880 --> 00:53:39,040
People like this
need to face someone like me.

828
00:53:39,120 --> 00:53:41,320
What kind of person
likes to look down on others?

829
00:53:42,680 --> 00:53:43,560
Pie!

830
00:53:44,080 --> 00:53:45,960
Take everything to our house!

831
00:53:46,040 --> 00:53:47,440
Don't leave a single thing behind.

832
00:53:52,120 --> 00:53:53,280
Let go of me!

833
00:53:53,360 --> 00:53:54,760
- I'm going back to deal with this.
- No, Mom.

834
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:58,440
Pie, don't. People like this
need to face someone like me.

835
00:53:58,520 --> 00:53:59,800
Don't go, Mom!

836
00:53:59,880 --> 00:54:01,080
Let go of me.

837
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:03,880
- Mom, can you please calm down?
- Pie, let go.

838
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:06,080
Pie!

839
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:08,920
Why are you dragging me away?
I'm not done with her yet.

840
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:10,440
Mom, please stop.

841
00:54:10,520 --> 00:54:12,280
Fighting won't help.

842
00:54:12,360 --> 00:54:14,160
Can we just let go of things?

843
00:54:14,240 --> 00:54:16,160
It's such a small thing,
not a big deal at all.

844
00:54:16,240 --> 00:54:17,280
Hey, Pie!

845
00:54:17,360 --> 00:54:20,120
Looking down on us like this
isn't a small thing.

846
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:21,960
But everything she said was true, Mom.

847
00:54:22,040 --> 00:54:25,320
But she shouldn't disrespect you,
especially not in front of the maids.

848
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:27,200
What will they think of you?

849
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:29,720
I don't care, Mom. I can handle it.

850
00:54:30,240 --> 00:54:32,520
Please, Mom, I'm begging you.

851
00:54:32,600 --> 00:54:36,680
If his mom is disrespectful again,
could you just ignore it?

852
00:54:36,760 --> 00:54:38,600
I don't want Pun to feel uncomfortable.

853
00:54:39,360 --> 00:54:41,200
Fine. Okay!

854
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:42,480
Sure, Pie.

855
00:54:42,560 --> 00:54:45,440
I'll try for the sake
of your love with Pun.

856
00:54:46,640 --> 00:54:49,000
Okay.

857
00:54:49,560 --> 00:54:50,800
Goodbye, Mom.

858
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:32,040
Pie.

859
00:56:33,560 --> 00:56:34,480
Pun.

860
00:56:35,920 --> 00:56:37,840
Why are you sleeping here in the dark?

861
00:56:42,040 --> 00:56:43,160
Take this.

862
00:56:43,920 --> 00:56:46,400
Flowers for my beautiful wife.

863
00:56:48,640 --> 00:56:50,160
Thank you, Pun.

864
00:56:57,040 --> 00:56:58,880
- Pun.
- Yes?

865
00:56:59,400 --> 00:57:00,680
I need to tell you something.

866
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:03,800
My mom and your mom fought today.

867
00:57:03,880 --> 00:57:06,000
My mom called me and told me already.

868
00:57:08,640 --> 00:57:09,480
Pie.

869
00:57:10,680 --> 00:57:13,920
Take it easy and learn at your own pace.

870
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:16,760
It's my fault

871
00:57:16,840 --> 00:57:20,880
for not briefing you beforehand
about the rules in my house.

872
00:57:22,160 --> 00:57:23,920
I have to be briefed?

873
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:26,880
Does your house
really have such strict rules?

874
00:57:28,160 --> 00:57:31,160
It's so everyone
can live together peacefully.

875
00:57:35,120 --> 00:57:37,800
Regarding receiving gifts or event money,

876
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:40,720
my mom has her own traditions
that have been passed down

877
00:57:40,800 --> 00:57:42,520
through generations.

878
00:57:42,600 --> 00:57:44,240
I forgot to tell you about this.

879
00:57:47,440 --> 00:57:48,400
Here's the plan.

880
00:57:48,920 --> 00:57:52,760
I'll slowly explain all the traditions
in my house to you.

881
00:57:53,800 --> 00:57:56,640
Today, I'll start by briefing you
on the meal etiquette.

882
00:57:56,720 --> 00:57:57,920
Huh?

883
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:00,520
Briefing about meals?

884
00:58:00,600 --> 00:58:02,520
Do we need a briefing about eating?

885
00:58:03,720 --> 00:58:04,640
Yes, we do.

886
00:58:12,800 --> 00:58:14,120
I want to order.

887
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:15,320
What can I get for you?

888
00:58:15,400 --> 00:58:16,680
Everything looks so good.

889
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:19,400
Do you like eating leftovers?

890
00:58:19,960 --> 00:58:23,400
Mink, you should've been
part of our family.

891
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,560
<i>I don't know how</i>
<i>he ended up marrying that girl.</i>

892
00:58:25,640 --> 00:58:27,120
<i>When is your next ovulation?</i>

893
00:58:27,200 --> 00:58:29,800
<i>Bring me your schedule so we can plan it.</i>

894
00:58:30,320 --> 00:58:32,000
<i>I'll try a new position</i>
<i>and see if it works.</i>

895
00:58:32,080 --> 00:58:33,880
<i>I want you to focus on the family.</i>

896
00:58:33,960 --> 00:58:35,440
<i>We're planning to have kids.</i>

897
00:58:35,520 --> 00:58:37,520
I think we're already way behind schedule.

898
00:58:42,880 --> 00:58:44,960
I don't like being betrayed!

899
00:58:45,040 --> 00:58:47,440
Anyone who makes me feel like I'm a fool,

900
00:58:47,520 --> 00:58:49,240
I don't keep them around!

901
00:59:14,280 --> 00:59:17,000
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
